      "role": "user",
      "content": "I get that those were the prejudices, but for the debate, I need to be able to present them effectively as \"logical\" arguments rather than just \"bigoted\" ones. If I'm arguing the side of the banks or the urban planners at the time, how would they have phrased the economic necessity of these decisions? Like, what were the specific \"rational\" arguments regarding community cohesion or fiscal responsibility they used to make it sound like a sound policy choice for the city? I need the actual structural logic they used to defend it.",
